#MTBPS Nene: Will help cities to improve living conditions, modernise transport/communications, promote trade & investment. SG
#MTBPS Nene: Capital injections for state owned companies will be allowed on condition of a sound business plan. SG
#MTBPS Nene: To avoid reducing expenditure, we need about R15bn a year in more revenue. Details in next budget. SG
#MTBPS: Nene: Planned spending on travel, conferences and catering has been cut. Advertising budgets reduced, will save R1.3bn over 2 yrs
#MTBPS: Nene Reduce the rate of growth to public entitites, particularles those with their own cash reserves. SG
#MTBPS Nene: Freeze budgets of non-essential goods and services at this years's levels, withdraw funding for long-vacant posts. SG
#MTBPS Nene's speech: Expenditure ceiling will be lowered by R10bn next year, and R15bn the year after. SG
#MTBPS Nene's speech: Consolidated budget deficit at R153, 4.1% of GPP. In line with Feb budget estimate. SG
#MTBPS Nene's speech: Total expenditure will be about R6bn less than Feb's estimate. Revised revenue estimate is R956 bn.
#MTBPS Nene's speech: R32mn for Ebola control, including help for affected countries. SG
#MTBPS Nene's speech: R157mn to Cooperative Governance to fix damaged infrastructure, R35mn for emergancy water interventions. SG
#MBTPS Nene's speech: Financial help to councils for free basic services will continue. SG
#MTBPS Nene's speech: Eskom will borrow R250bn over next five years. Govt provide R20bn through sale of non-strategic assets. SG
#MTBPS: Nene's speech: Building capacity & accountability in public sector critical, particularly at local government level. SG
#MTBPS From Nene's text: Quality of education and health systems needs be improved. SG
#MTBPS Nene: We are helping companies update their factories and equipment. SG
#MTBPS Nene: We must shift from consumption led growth, to investment led growth. SG
#MTBPS Nene: This budget is aimed at restoring balance to the nation's finances. SG
#MTBPS Nene: When we gave the budget, we said growth at 2.7%. Now expecting only 1.4%. SG
#mtbps Nene: This is a difficult time, govts everywhere are looking at how to create growth. We have to do more with less. SG
#MTBPS Nene does a shout-out to new Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago. Nice. SG
#MTBPS And we're off, the Finance Minister Nhanhla Nene: Thank you Honourable Speaker. SG
